doc.after: The affinities of the Mascarene parrot are unclear, and two hypotheses have competed since the mid-19th century.[11] Some authors grouped it with the Coracopsinae (of African origin) due to its dark plumage, and others with the Psittaculinae parrots (of Asian origin) based on the large red beak, a feature which is diagnostic for that group.[6][12] Its plumage pattern was mostly atypical for a psittaculine, though other members have black facial patterns.[2]
